CONTENTS &#183; BIBLIOGRAPHIC RECORD







Gerard Manley Hopkins (1844&#150;89).  Poems.  1918.
 
32.  Spelt from Sibyl's Leaves
  









 
EARNEST, earthless, equal, attuneable, ' vaulty, voluminous, &#133; stupendous
Evening strains to be t&iacute;me's v&aacute;st, ' womb-of-all, home-of-all, hearse-of-all night.
Her fond yellow hornlight wound to the west, ' her wild hollow hoarlight hung to the height
Waste; her earliest stars, earl-stars, ' st&aacute;rs principal, overbend us,
F&iacute;re-f&eacute;aturing heaven. For earth ' her being has unbound, her dapple is at an end, as-        5
tray or aswarm, all throughther, in throngs; ' self &iacute;n self steed&egrave;d and p&aacute;shed&#151;q&uacute;ite
Disremembering, d&iacute;sm&eacute;mbering ' &aacute;ll now. Heart, you round me right
With: &Oacute;ur &eacute;vening is over us; &oacute;ur night ' wh&eacute;lms, wh&eacute;lms, &aacute;nd will end us.
Only the beak-leaved boughs dragonish ' damask the tool-smooth bleak light; black,
Ever so black on it. &Oacute;ur tale, O &oacute;ur oracle! ' L&eacute;t life, w&aacute;ned, ah l&eacute;t life wind        10
Off h&eacute;r once sk&eacute;ined stained v&eacute;ined variety ' upon, &aacute;ll on tw&oacute; spools; p&aacute;rt, pen, p&aacute;ck
Now her &aacute;ll in tw&oacute; flocks, tw&oacute; folds&#151;black, white; ' right, wrong; reckon but, reck but, mind
But th&eacute;se two; w&aacute;re of a w&oacute;rld where b&uacute;t these ' tw&oacute; tell, each off the &oacute;ther; of a rack
Where, selfwrung, selfstrung, sheathe- and shelterless, ' th&oacute;ughts aga&iacute;nst thoughts &iacute;n groans gr&iacute;nd.


 See Notes.

 











