Gerard Manley Hopkins (1844&#150;89).  Poems.  1918.
 
62.  &#145;Denis, whose motionable, alert, most vaulting wit'
  









 
DENIS, whose motionable, alert, most vaulting wit
Caps occasion with an intellectual fit.
Yet Arthur is a Bowman: his three-heeled timber 'll hit
The bald and b&oacute;ld bl&iacute;nking gold when &aacute;ll 's d&oacute;ne
Right rooting in the bare butt's wincing navel in the sight of the sun.   .   .   .   .   .   .   .   .        5


 See Notes.

 











