Gerard Manley Hopkins (1844&#150;89).  Poems.  1918.
 
71.  &#145;Strike, churl; hurl, cheerless wind, then; heltering hail'
  









 
STRIKE, churl; hurl, cheerless wind, then; heltering hail
May's beauty massacre and wisp&egrave;d wild clouds grow
Out on the giant air; tell Summer No,
Bid joy back, have at the harvest, keep Hope pale.


 See Notes.

 











